Madam President, dear colleagues! I am a little surprised at the behavior of Mr Barón Crespo, who is now asking for this item to be placed on Wednesday's agenda.
Mr Barón Crespo, you were unable to be present at the Conference of Presidents last Thursday.
I am not criticizing that; it always happens that you are represented.
Your colleague Hänsch represented you there.
We had an extensive debate in the Conference of Presidents.
Your group alone represented what you are now saying.
We then voted.
Each chairman has as many votes as the group has members.
There was a vote on this point.
As far as I can remember, this vote went like this: 422 votes to 180 with a few abstentions.
In other words, all the groups, with the exception of the non-attached group - but they are not a group - agreed that only your group was of the opinion that we should proceed as you have proposed here.
Everyone else disagreed.
